This paper discusses modeling the Semantic Web using a type system, which involves symbolic representation and inductive reasoning over data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) for the machine learning aspect, Databases (cs.DB) for the data representation and querying, Machine Learning (cs.LG) for the use of analytics, Software Engineering (cs.SE) for the inference engine, and Programming Languages (cs.PL) for the type system itself.
